{{Quote|For every plant that was destroyed in the harvest, two must be planted to replace it|[[Momaw Nadon/Legends|Momaw Nadon]] reciting the Ithorian's 'Law of Life'|<ref name="The Sand Tender: The Hammerhead's Tale">{{StoryCite|story=The Sand Tender: The Hammerhead's Tale|book=Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina}}</ref>}}
The '''Law of Life''' was an [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] belief.

The Law said that, for every living [[Plant/Legends|plant]] destroyed in the harvest, two more must be planted in its place. However, Ithorian use of this Law went much farther than harvests: For every life, be it a plant or an animal, an Ithorian might take, during a harvest or not, two new lives were to be created in its place.

Ithorian [[Momaw Nadon/Legends|Momaw Nadon]] was forced to betray [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial officer/Legends|officer]] [[Alima]] so that Alima was executed. This was completely against his beliefs. To atone his sin, Nadon stole samples of Alima's DNA and cloned him, creating two clones of Alima.

Similarly, the entity known as [[Spore]] was captured by Ithorians after centuries of struggle during which Spore killed hundreds of people. However, as Ithorians were unable to clone Spore or provide an equivalent life using any means, they could not kill Spore, but only bury it.

